To ensure the **Quantum Protocol** operates securely while allowing the client-side transactions (ROI processing, package purchases, and bonus claims) to function, you must deploy the following rules.

These rules implement a **Defense-in-Depth** strategy:
1.  **Identity Isolation**: Users can only read/write their own sensitive data.
2.  **Admin Escalation**: Only accounts with the `isAdmin` flag (defined in the database) can access the system vault, modify node configurations, or view the global user list.
3.  **Transaction Integrity**: Rules for `giveawayClaims` and `activePackages` ensure users can only create records tied to their own unique `auth.uid`.

### Firestore Security Rules

Copy and paste the following into your **Firebase Console > Firestore > Rules** tab:

```javascript
rules_version = '2';

service cloud.firestore {
  match /databases/{database}/documents {

    // Helper: Check if user is an authenticated administrator
    function isAdmin() {
      return request.auth != null && 
        get(/databases/$(database)/documents/users/$(request.auth.uid)).data.isAdmin == true;
    }

    // Helper: Check if the document belongs to the authenticated user
    function isOwner(userId) {
      return request.auth != null && request.auth.uid == userId;
    }

    // --- USERS COLLECTION ---
    match /users/{userId} {
      // Users can read/write their own profile. Admins can manage all.
      allow read, write: if isOwner(userId) || isAdmin();
    }

    // --- TRANSACTIONS COLLECTION ---
    match /transactions/{txId} {
      // Allow creation of transactions by authenticated users (for deposits/purchases)
      allow create: if request.auth != null && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;
      // Admins can create transactions for any user (credits/sweeps)
      allow create: if isAdmin();
      // Users can only read their own transaction history. Admins see all.
      allow read: if isAdmin() || (request.auth != null && resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid);
      // Transactions should never be updated or deleted by users
      allow update, delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- PACKAGES (NODE CONFIGS) ---
    match /packages/{pkgId} {
      // Everyone can see available nodes
      allow read: if true;
      // Only admins can add, edit, or delete node tiers
      allow write: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- ACTIVE PACKAGES (USER SUBSCRIPTIONS) ---
    match /activePackages/{apId} {
      // Users can manage their own node activations
      allow read, write: if isAdmin() || (request.auth != null && (
        resource == null ? request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid : resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid
      ));
    }

    // --- GIVEAWAY POOLS ---
    match /giveawayPools/{poolId} {
      // Users need to read pools to verify codes
      allow read: if request.auth != null;
      // Only admins manage pools
      allow write: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- GIVEAWAY CLAIMS ---
    match /giveawayClaims/{claimId} {
      // Users can create claims for themselves
      allow create: if request.auth != null && request.resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid;
      // Users can check if they've already claimed
      allow read: if isAdmin() || (request.auth != null && resource.data.userId == request.auth.uid);
      allow update, delete: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- SYSTEM SETTINGS & STATUS ---
    match /system/{document} {
      // Public settings like ROI status and Platform Pause
      allow read: if true;
      // Only admins can change system-wide settings
      allow write: if isAdmin();
      // Special case: Initializing the first admin
      allow create: if request.auth != null && document == 'status';
    }

    // --- VAULT (HOT WALLET KEYS) ---
    match /vault/{document} {
      // Strictly restricted to Admin only. Contains private keys.
      allow read, write: if isAdmin();
    }

    // --- DEFAULT DENY ---
    match /{path=**} {
      allow read, write: if isAdmin();
    }
  }
}
```

### Deployment Checklist:
1.  **First User**: Ensure the very first user you register has the email `admin` in it, or manually toggle the `isAdmin` boolean to `true` in the Firestore console for your account to gain access to the **Admin Panel**.
2.  **Indexes**: Firebase might prompt you in the browser console to "Create an Index" for certain queries (like filtering transactions by `userId`). Click the link provided in the console error to generate them automatically.
3.  **Hot Wallet**: Go to the **Admin Panel > Overview** and ensure your Hot Wallet address is set up so the withdrawal system knows where to send funds from.

